---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Features | Qibla Now"
  description="Prayer times, Qibla direction, map support, alarms, location modes, and focused settings in Qibla Now."
>
  <section class="section">
    <p class="eyebrow">Features</p>
    <h1>Focused capabilities for daily prayer use.</h1>
    <p>
      Qibla Now concentrates on the essential functions: prayer times, Qibla direction,
      alarms, map support, and precise settings without unnecessary complexity.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="grid-2">
      <div>
        <h2>Prayer times</h2>
        <p>
          Accurate daily prayer schedules with configurable calculation methods, madhab selection,
          and high-latitude rules. All calculations are performed locally, with no backend dependency.
        </p>
      </div>
      <img src="/screenshots/home.png" alt="Qibla Now prayer times screen" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="grid-2">
      <div>
        <h2>Qibla direction</h2>
        <p>
          Qibla Now uses great-circle bearing toward the Kaaba, shown through compass, map, and numeric direction. The map view illustrates the true geodesic line, not a straight line on a flat map.
        </p>
      </div>
      <img src="/screenshots/map.png" alt="Qibla Now Qibla map screen" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="grid-2">
      <div>
        <h2>Notifications and alarms</h2>
        <p>
          Local notification scheduling for prayer times, with no cloud dependency. Alarms are reliable and configurable, respecting device battery and privacy constraints.
        </p>
      </div>
      <img src="/screenshots/notification-settings.png" alt="Qibla Now notification settings" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="grid-2">
      <div>
        <h2>Location modes</h2>
        <p>
          Multiple location modes: device GPS, manual entry, and saved locations. All modes are designed for privacy and offline-first use.
        </p>
      </div>
      <img src="/screenshots/location-settings.png" alt="Qibla Now location settings" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="grid-2">
      <div>
        <h2>Settings and calculation controls</h2>
        <p>
          Deep configuration: calculation method, madhab, high-latitude rules, display options, and notification preferences. All settings are stored locally and never sent to a backend.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="settings-gallery">
        <img src="/screenshots/display-settings.png" alt="Qibla Now display settings" />
        <img src="/screenshots/calculation-settings.png" alt="Qibla Now calculation settings" />
        <img src="/screenshots/settings.png" alt="Qibla Now general settings" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
.settings-gallery {
  display: flex;
  gap: 1rem;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  margin-top: 0.5rem;
}
.settings-gallery img {
  width: 140px;
  border-radius: 8px;
  background: #f8f6ee;
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
}
</style>